



To Ensign Milner.
[Winchester, 4 May 1756]



You are hereby ordered to proceed to Cunningham-Fort, and there to use your utmost endeavours to engage one or two good woodsmen to serve as pilots to the Detachment under Captain Woodward.1 I have been told that a Son of Colonel Morgan,2 now at that place, will answer the intention full well; him you are to endeavour to getIf they insist upon certain pay before they stir, you must engage it to them: and are to Order that they meet the party on Back-Creek. Given at Winchester, May 4th 1756.

G:W.

